<item>
            <title>[AMQ-5951] failover maxReconnect=0 url can block on reconnect</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-5951</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;client with &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;failover:(tcp:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//localhost:61616)?maxReconnectAttempts=0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;with exception listener that attempts to use the connection, ie: do a rollback/ack/shutdown, can block pending transport close.&lt;br/&gt;
A retrying failover oneway send will block the mutex transport in error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
